First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden are celebrating the 5th anniversary of their Joining Forces initiative. They have made commitments with over 50 companies to hire and train veterans and military spouses in various fields. Jeff Bezos, the founder and CEO of Amazon.com, will announce Amazon's employment and training commitment to veterans and military spouses. There will also be a USO comedy show hosted by Jon Stewart, featuring David Letterman and other comedians, to celebrate Military Appreciation Month and the 5th anniversary of Joining Forces. The First Lady will join Prince Harry to celebrate the Opening Ceremonies of the 2016 Invictus Games, an international adaptive sporting event for wounded, injured, and ill service members and veterans.